OL,4,Cillegally, campaign footage shows
OL,6,FFor over a decade, the company
OL,7,FWhiteshore Cockles has been burying
OL,8,Fdead and diseased salmon from fish
OL,9,Ffarms in pits of sand and seaweed.
OL,11,FBurial was legal due to an exemption
OL,12,Ffrom the Scottish Government, and with
OL,13,Fthe understanding that Whiteshore
OL,14,FCockles was building a fish waste
OL,15,Fdryer.
